    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted given the ASTM F1717 standardized quasi-static protocol and the Medium model risk classification. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. The FEA model ensemble is deemed credible for the defined COU.",
